        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Oct 27<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I have heard from the Treasury, that they are ready to pay to you 40<hi rend="superscript">£</hi>’4<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> ’5<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>.— <ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The final payment of the Treasury grant for <hi rend="italic">Zoology.</hi> See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-702A.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to A. Y. Spearman, 9 October 1843</ref>, n. 1, and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-702.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Smith, Elder &amp; Co., [9 October 1843]</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
